(2, 'Atri', 'atri', '<h1>Atri - The Revered Sage</h1>', '<p>Atri is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian culture. Here\\\'s some key information about Atri:</p>    <h2>Life and Legends</h2>    <p>Atri was born to the divine sage <strong>Brahma</strong> and is considered one of the seven sages (<em>Saptarishis</em>) who have guided humanity throughout history. He is often depicted as a wise and powerful sage with a long beard.</p>    <h2>Contributions</h2>    <ul>      <li><strong>Vedic Wisdom:</strong> Atri is credited with composing several hymns in the <em>Rigveda</em>, one of Hinduism\\\'s most sacred texts.</li>        <li><strong>Ayurveda:</strong> He is associated with the development of Ayurveda, the traditional Indian system of medicine.</li>        <li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Atri is revered as a spiritual guru, offering guidance on the path to enlightenment.</li> </ul>    <h2>Family and Descendants</h2>    <ul>       <li><strong>Wife:</strong> Atri\\\'s wife was <em>Anasuya</em>, a pious and devoted woman who was known for her extraordinary spiritual powers.</li>  <li><strong>Sons:</strong> Atri and Anasuya had three sons: <em>Dattatreya, Durvasa,</em> and <em>Chandra</em>.</li>   <li><strong>Descendants:</strong> Atri\\\'s descendants are considered to be the <em>Atri clan</em>, which includes many notable sages and seers in Hindu mythology.</li>  </ul>   <h2>Worship and Legacy</h2>  <ul>    <li><strong>Temples:</strong> Atri is worshipped in several temples across India, particularly in the states of Maharashtra and Gujarat.</li>       <li><strong>Festivals:</strong> His birthday, <em>Atri Jayanti</em>, is celebrated with great fervor in some parts of India.</li>   <li><strong>Influence on Culture:</strong> Atri\\\'s contributions to Hindu mythology, Ayurveda, and spiritual guidance have had a lasting impact on Indian heritage.</li> </ul>    <p>Atri\\\'s life an