(3, 'Ashtavakra', 'ashtavakra', '<h1>Ashtavakra - The Revered Sage</h1>', '<p>Ashtavakra is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian philosophy. Here\\\'s some key information about Ashtavakra:</p> <h2>Life and Legends</h2>   <p>Ashtavakra was born with eight physical deformities (<em>ashta-vakra</em> means \\\"eight bends\\\" in Sanskrit), which made him an outcast in society. Despite his physical limitations, he possessed extraordinary spiritual powers and wisdom.</p>   <h2>Contributions</h2>    <ul> <li><strong>Ashtavakra Gita:</strong> Ashtavakra is credited with composing the <em>Ashtavakra Gita</em>, a sacred text that explores the nature of reality, the self, and the path to enlightenment.</li>       <li><strong>Advaita Vedanta:</strong> His teachings are rooted in <em>Advaita Vedanta</em>, a school of Hindu philosophy that emphasizes the non-dual nature of reality.</li>        <li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Ashtavakra is revered as a spiritual guru, offering guidance on the path to self-realization and enlightenment.</li>  </ul>   <h2>Meeting with King Janaka</h2>    <p>Ashtavakra\\\'s most famous encounter was with <strong>King Janaka</strong>, a powerful and wise ruler who was seeking spiritual guidance. Ashtavakra\\\'s teachings had a profound impact on King Janaka, who eventually attained enlightenment.</p>    <h2>Teachings and Philosophy</h2>    <p>Ashtavakra\\\'s teachings emphasize the importance of:</p>    <ul>    <li><strong>Self-inquiry:</strong> Investigating the nature of the self and reality.</li>        <li><strong>Non-dualism:</strong> Recognizing the non-dual nature of reality, beyond distinctions and separations.</li>       <li><strong>Detachment:</strong> Letting go of attachments and desires that bind us to the material world.</li>    </ul>   <h2>Legacy and Influence</h2>    <p>Ashtavakra\\\'s teachings have had a profound impact on Hindu philosophy and spirituality, influencing many notable sages and philosophers, including <strong>Adi Shankara</strong>. His legacy continues to inspire seekers of truth and self-realization.</p>', '1740906741_Ashtavakra.jpg'),
(4, 'Kapila', 'kapila', '&lt;h1&gt;Kapila - The Revered Sage&lt;/h1&gt;', '<p>Kapila is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian philosophy. Here\'s some key information about Kapila:</p> <h2>Life and Legends</h2> <p>Kapila was born to the sage <strong>Kardama</strong> and his wife, <strong>Devahuti</strong>. He is considered one of the seven sages (<em>Saptarishis</em>) who have guided humanity throughout history.</p><h2>Contributions</h2> <ul> <li><strong>Sankhya Philosophy:</strong> Kapila is credited with developing the <em>Sankhya</em> philosophy, one of the six orthodox schools of Hindu philosophy. Sankhya emphasizes the dual nature of reality, comprising <em>purusha</em> (consciousness) and <em>prakriti</em> (matter).</li> <li><strong>Mahabharata:</strong> Kapila appears in the <em>Mahabharata</em>, where he plays a significant role in the story of King Sagara and the descent of the Ganges River.</li> <li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Kapila is revered as a spiritual guru, offering guidance on the path to self-realization and enlightenment.</li> </ul><h2>Meeting with Devahuti</h2> <p>Kapila\'s most famous encounter was with his mother, <strong>Devahuti</strong>, who sought his guidance on spiritual matters. Kapila\'s teachings had a profound impact on Devahuti, who eventually attained enlightenment.</p> <h2>Teachings and Philosophy</h2> <p>Kapila\'s teachings emphasize the importance of:</p> <ul> <li><strong>Discrimination:</strong> Distinguishing between the eternal and the ephemeral, the self and the non-self.</li> <li><strong>Detachment:</strong> Letting go of attachments and desires that bind us to the material world.</li> <li><strong>Self-realization:</strong> Recognizing the true nature of the self and reality.</li> </ul> <h2>Legacy and Influence</h2> <p>Kapila\'s teachings have had a profound impact on Hindu philosophy and spirituality, influencing many notable sages an