(13, 'Dadhichi', 'dadhichi', '&lt;h1&gt;Dadhichi - The Revered Sage&lt;/h1&gt;', '<p>Dadhichi is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian mythology.</p><h2>Life and Legends</h2><p>Dadhichi was a powerful sage who lived in ancient India. He was a <strong>Brahmarishi</strong> (a sage with divine powers) and was known for his extraordinary spiritual abilities.</p><h2>Contributions</h2><ul><li><strong>Vedic Literature:</strong> Dadhichi is credited with composing several hymns and verses in the <em>Rigveda</em>, one of the most sacred texts of Hinduism.</li><li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Dadhichi was a spiritual guide who offered wisdom and enlightenment to seekers.</li><li><strong>Donation of Bones:</strong> Dadhichi is famous for donating his bones to the gods, which were used to create the <em>Vajra</em>, the thunderbolt of Lord Indra.</li></ul><h2>Teachings and Philosophy</h2><p>Dadhichi\'s teachings emphasize the importance of:</p><ul><li><strong>Selflessness:</strong> Letting go of one\'s ego and desires for the greater good.</li><li><strong>Detachment:</strong> Detaching oneself from worldly attachments and desires.</li><li><strong>Spiritual Growth:</strong> Pursuing spiritual growth and self-realization through meditation, yoga, and other spiritual practices.</li></ul><h2>Legacy and Influence</h2><p>Dadhichi\'s legacy continues to inspire seekers of truth and self-realization. His teachings and philosophy have had a profound impact on Hindu mythology, Vedic literature, and spirituality.</p><h2>Interesting Facts</h2><ul><li><strong>Name Meaning:</strong> The name <em>\"Dadhichi\"</em> means \"one who gives\" in Sanskrit.</li><li><strong>Association with Indra:</strong> Dadhichi is often associated with Lord Indra, the Hindu god of thunder, and is said to have possessed the power to communicate with him.</li><li><strong>Mention in Mahabharata:</strong> Dadhichi is mentioned in the <em>Mahabharata</em>, one of the most sacred texts of Hinduism.</li></ul>', 'Dadhichi.jpg'),
(14, 'Vishvamitra', 'vishvamitra', '&lt;h1&gt;Vishvamitra - The Revered Sage&lt;/h1&gt;', '<p>Vishvamitra is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian mythology and Vedic literature.</p><h2>Life and Legends</h2><p>Vishvamitra was a powerful sage who lived in ancient India. He was a <strong>Brahmarishi</strong> (a sage with divine powers) and was known for his extraordinary spiritual abilities.</p><h2>Family and Descendants</h2><p>Vishvamitra was a king who renounced his throne to become a sage. He had several sons, including:</p><ul><li><strong>Madhucchanda:</strong> A sage known for his wisdom and spiritual powers.</li><li><strong>Devarata:</strong> A sage known for his wisdom and spiritual powers.</li><li><strong>Shunashepa:</strong> A sage known for his wisdom and spiritual powers.</li></ul><h2>Contributions</h2><ul><li><strong>Vedic Literature:</strong> Vishvamitra is credited with composing several hymns and verses in the <em>Rigveda</em>, one of the most sacred texts of Hinduism.</li><li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Vishvamitra was a spiritual guide who offered wisdom and enlightenment to seekers.</li><li><strong>Test of Brahma:</strong> Vishvamitra is said to have tested the creator god Brahma\'s powers and was granted the title of <em>\"Rajarishi\"</em> (royal sage).</li></ul><h2>Teachings and Philosophy</h2><p>Vishvamitra\'s teachings emphasize the importance of:</p><ul><li><strong>Self-realization:</strong> Attaining spiritual enlightenment and self-awareness.</li><li><strong>Dharma:</strong> Living a righteous and virtuous life.</li><li><strong>Yoga:</strong> Practicing yoga and meditation to attain spiritual growth and self-realization.</li></ul><h2>Legacy and Influence</h2><p>Vishvamitra\'s legacy continues to inspire seekers of truth and self-realization. His teachings and philosophy have had a profound impact on Hindu mythology, Vedic literature, and spirituality.</p><