(15, 'Kanva', 'kanva', '&lt;h1&gt;Kanva - The Revered Sage&lt;/h1&gt;', '<p> Kanva is a revered sage in Hinduism, known for his extraordinary wisdom, spiritual powers, and contributions to ancient Indian mythology and Vedic literature. Here\'s some key information about Kanva: </p> <h2>Life and Legends</h2><p>Kanva was a powerful sage who lived in ancient India. He was a brahmarishi (a sage with divine powers) and was known for his extraordinary spiritual abilities.</p><h2>Family and Descendants</h2><p>Kanva was the foster father of Shakuntala, a legendary heroine of Hindu mythology. He was also the father of several other notable sages and seers.</p><h2>Contributions</h2><ul><li><strong>Vedic Literature:</strong> Kanva is credited with composing several hymns and verses in the Rigveda, one of the most sacred texts of Hinduism.</li><li><strong>Spiritual Guidance:</strong> Kanva was a spiritual guide who offered guidance and wisdom to those seeking enlightenment.</li><li><strong>Education of Shakuntala:</strong> Kanva played a significant role in the education and upbringing of Shakuntala, who was abandoned by her mother, Menaka, and was found and adopted by Kanva.</li></ul><h2>Teachings and Philosophy</h2><p>Kanva\'s teachings emphasize the importance of:</p><ul><li><strong>Self-realization:</strong> Attaining spiritual enlightenment and self-awareness.</li><li><strong>Dharma:</strong> Living a righteous and virtuous life.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Compassion:</strong> Showing kindness and compassion to all living beings.</li></ul><h2>Legacy and Influence</h2><p>Kanva\'s legacy continues to inspire seekers of truth and self-realization. His teachings and philosophy have had a profound impact on Hindu mythology, Vedic literature, and spirituality.</p><h2>Interesting Facts</h2><ul><li><strong>Name Meaning:</strong> The name \"Kanva\" means \"wise\" or \"intelligent\" in Sanskrit.</li><li><strong>Association with Shakuntala:</strong> Kanva is often associated with Shakuntala